All Implemented Interfaces:
Entity, Relation, Comparable<Relation>
@Entity(name="Program")
@Relation(name="\"scetris\".\"Program\"",
          requiredSqlCols={"academic_term","department","program_manager"})
@XmlElement(value="Program")
public class Program
extends GenericEntity
implements Entity

OO-Representation of the entity-relation Program

A Program is a set of CourseInstances. It has a running period (start and end date). A program manager is responsible for a Program. A Program belongs to a Department and to one Department only.

setAcademicTerm

public Program setAcademicTerm(AcademicTerm value)
Sets the value of academicTerm. If the new value is the same as the old value, this method has no effect, i.e. if you specify a new value, than isAcademicTermChanged() will return true. If you specify the same value as the old value isAcademicTermChanged() will return the same as it did before calling setAcademicTerm(...).

Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the value is null (since academicTerm is not nullable)
